org.opengis.cite.securityclient10.httpServer

Class ServerOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opengis.cite.securityclient10.httpServer.ServerOptions

  • public class ServerOptions
extends Object
    Class for options passed to emulated server types in TestServer. Used to specify all Requirement Classes from the Web Services Security Standard that will apply on the test run.

        public int getExpectedRequestCount()
        Determine the number of client requests to expect for a given type of authentication scheme. For SAML2, the IdP URL must also be defined. None - 1 request Saml2 - 3 requests

      • setAuthentication

        public void setAuthentication(String auth)
        Set the authentication method. If a blank string or null, then no authentication method will be applied. Currently valid values are "none" and "saml2".
        Parameters:

      • setIdpUrl

        public void setIdpUrl(String url)
        Set the Identity Provider SSO resource URL. If a blank string, then null is used and the parameter is omitted from the emulated server.
        Parameters:
        url - A string with the URL to the Identity Provider SSO resource.
